  "texts": [
    "In the 1990 s, early studies relied on rule-based expert systems and basic statistical pattern recognition to support the development of electronic noses and tongues.",
    "During the 2000 s, machine learning methods such as support vector machines and decision trees were increasingly used for classifying odors and tastants.",
    "More recently, deep learning models have enabled the processing of complex, highdimensional sensory data, leading to significant improvements in prediction accuracy and scalability.",
    "This historical progression highlights how advances in AI methodologies have steadily enhanced the precision, applicability, and realism of sensory modeling.A growing body of research draws inspiration from the biological foundations of sensory processing.",
    "For example, biologically motivated deep learning algorithms simulate how the brain interprets chemical signals from smell and taste receptors (Bartunov et al. 2018)."
